sents about seventy realized structures from the last three decades. Drawing upon his in-depth knowledge of the subject and his many years of publishing experience, the author offers a valuable analysis of the conceptual and formal aspects that combine to create the religious impact of spaces (e.g., the ground plan, the shapes of the spaces, the incidence of light, and materiality).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aarchitecture. 4achurches. 4amosques. 4asynagogues. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aBaumann, Dorothea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAKIM, NEGAR, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHollenstein, Roman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKREUZ, EVA-MARIA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNiederstätter, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AND ARCHITECTURE 2008z978311031899908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET KUNST UND ARCHITEKTUR 2008z9783110318890oZDB-23-DKA0 cprintz978376438819540uhttps://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7643-8276-640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783764382766423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783764382766/original  a